{
  "text": "Changes in annual temperature, annual precipitation and maximum climatological water deficit (MCWD 100 ) were calculated, as these have been found to be good indicators of humid tropical forest extent [CITATION_1] . Local changes were related to global mean temperature increase (DT g ). Area-averages were used to explore the range of model projections for regions with contrasting signals in the ensemble means.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "2548249"
